                    <h3>RULES FOR PROMOTION</h3>
                    <p class="desc2">1. For Middle school students (Classes V to VIII), a student should get at least D grade in each subject.<br>2. For Secondary Section students (Class IX to X), a student should get at least D grade in each subject according to CBSE Board normes.<br>3. For Senior Secondary Section students (Class XI), a student should get at least 33% marks in each subject (separately in theory and practical) with an aggregate of 33% marks.<br>4. Weightage for Calculation of Final Result.&nbsp; Class V to X<br>Formative Assessments (F1, F2, F3 &amp; F4) : 10% each<br>Summative Assessments - 1 &amp; 2 : 30% each<br>It is mandatory to get 25% marks in SA1 &amp; SA2 in order to qualify for next class.<br>5. The academic performance of the students of classes V to X will be evaluated according to the following absolute grading system (As per CBSE guideline)<br>Class VI - X<br>Marks Grade<br>91-100 A1<br>81-90A2<br>71-80B1<br>61-70B2<br>51-60C1<br>41-50C2<br>33-40D<br>21-32E1<br>00-20E2<br>The result cards for Classes V to X will be filled up according to the gradation system. Under no circumstances the aggregate marks obtained by the child will be intimated.<br>6. Students found using unfair means during any weekly test or term examinations will be marked Zero in that subject. No retest will be held for such students. These students will not be eligible for any academic award or school appointment.<br>Note<br>(1) A Child who fails twice in the same class will not be permitted to continue in the school. Transfer certificate will be issued to him or her.<br>(2) If attendance is less than 75% the child will not be allowed to appear in the annual examination.</p>
